[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying class mapping**\n\nI'm trying to clarify the idea of \"one-to-one mapping between report classes and generated test class files.\" It seems to suggest that I shouldn't create separate test class files. Instead, maybe I can create a class within the same test file as package-private? However, I know there might be issues if ObjectWithFieldsConverter fails to instantiate due to it being non-public. If that’s the case, what about a string converter? Also, if the child has no children, could it affect class loading?\n\n**Considering converters and configurations**\n\nI need to use CollectionConverter from Configuration with DefaultConverterLookup along with a registered custom converter to avoid issues with ObjectWithFields. However, I see that the registerConverter method in DefaultConverterLookup is public. I might have to define a converter specifically for Element classes. Also, I need to think about the ExpressionEvaluator — perhaps it can be null? I think the fromExpression method handles the expression evaluator. I need to inspect AbstractConfigurationConverter further.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_057c211ae7f8ece8016a04008c10bc8195b4bf294eff8f2271\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBACZue_jPKAqsBxSJXNA9YibuHnUTgTWRzIcDK34f6KiPpzI6YW0NDhfhF4I0qISW5DSy6xaERaRrJ5M7Z8pvXDmHhQjzaWS5bFyEmREWEoeueq270jC25mwRIrlQGCAi-UDTrKbz3Fe6QFkxPe1kIr1jx1aaTYDzfHJYH4TFJxxqyuNQ_Bri0ic9MW9oGT2VbRzFC3MSNDY2QF769bKymu8MZw41mKNYE6vD43tU3ADiZ8UeXZCmDCXlmD5y2dT8caFKIxmHYOJn_dzS2UyEFy1k6kCf4f3V5ZxQnEOTDMsF-IVkWfVGnrAQlKM3CC-cPxNYnEYEedVbWZyjvNQKZ09C6KBMbhxNk599M4qOdRpf7WIHxgVJO53MifMWvhD9ntUF1gO6bTM3gt22OiF4SLcm_NmVMta2raJHe9RYzlDDjU9fC1DoDF63NC-FNArFVCmUwQaaW08Jb_ZQFUQ0W0QEZ0_n0vAdM0Zq0t546_0eXufCGBQczpv6Kl0niFUtsgJ09SYWp-IL-BfF8lfSdW_Ai8TfWFYn6T_usnX2MXDcW29j35H2aIjcSbDuJ6RiDdpZLvFaeTSYa57QqJXUZKbzv4Gv1tL-jM2F5QzfnTWEqiCNmvT7tVwmL5LxdeDGp2jB